While some aspects of the vocal search are opinion-based, the blog will at least be internally consistent! Additionally, every search should randomize the order of posts so people can discover new vocals every time! :)

You can search based on a variety of options including language, engine, vocal qualities (the 3 I have right now are gender, strength, and maturity), and vocal range! it uses the tag system and hidden post text to filter them (you should see my spreadsheet of tags)

20. I had the most fun tuning my song Standing With You! It was a really fun song and getting Rana to sing in English is really tough so I had a lot of fun with the challenge! 

https://t.co/BHERDsCN99
19. I'm currently trying to improve my music! But I'm just taking it easy :) i dont want to take it super seriously because I would like to keep music a simple hobby that does not stress me out haha
18. I like tuning English a lot!! there's just so much nuance to add and mess with that its a fun challenge every time
17. I do tend to sing while I tune! probably why my tuning is mid (I am not a singer LOL) but it helps a little!

16. I struggle to get SONIKA to sound the way I want her to - so I end up avoiding using her :') i wouldnt say shes hard to tune, just hard to get her how I want exactly because I think the sonika in my head and the sonika in reality dont exactly match up LOL
@charcolor thank u so much , i just really think shes neat
15. For me SOLARIA and Rana are my easiest voicebanks to use, just because I'm so familiar with both of them!

14. I have always found my friend khanadee's expressive tuning to be really impressive & I'd like to go more in that direction! Obviously im also really impressed by more well known tuners like KIRA, Cillia and Rishie as well - but tbh I dont have time to focus on tuning much!

13. I think a good voicebank is really made by versatility! But also I have a soft spot for cutesy vocals, and I love pretty much every vocal synth because I just think its all so cool !!!! no bad vocal synths

12. I've been working through my VOCALOID wishlist recently, but I still hope to get my hands on YANHE and Otomachi Una! I also will probably get Kevin and Ryo soon once I get time to use them, and I'd like to buy KAFU and IA English but I need to see how CeVIO Pro goes first!
(of course , its probably more challenging because its my first language as well so when something sounds off its immediately clear to me)

11. my favorite songs to tune are my own! i like messing with things in detail while I can also adjust the entire project - in general though I prefer to tune in English because its more challenging than other languages ive tuned! which gives me more to mess around with
